01:16.576 --> 01:18.378 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We're glad to
have you.

01:18.412 --> 01:22.549 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, our top story tonight:
President Trump's
push for a wall on the border
with Mexico

01:22.582 --> 01:27.821 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has opened a diplomatic rift,
and it raises
the prospect of a major new tax.

01:27.854 --> 01:29.556 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins begins our
coverage.

01:29.589 --> 01:33.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), President of
the United
States: The president of Mexico
and myself

01:33.593 --> 01:37.564 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have agreed to cancel our
planned meeting
scheduled for next week.

01:37.597 --> 01:41.134 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: That was the
president's
version of events today.

01:41.168 --> 01:47.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hours earlier, Mexican President
Enrique Pena
Nieto canceled his scheduled
visit to Washington.

01:47.140 --> 01:51.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He'd come under heavy political
pressure at
home after Mr. Trump signed an
executive order

01:51.912 --> 01:57.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on Wednesday to start work on a
border wall,
and insisted again that Mexico
will ultimately

01:57.751 --> 01:59.553 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
pay for it.

01:59.586 --> 02:03.423 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, the president gave no
ground at the
congressional Republican retreat
in Philadelphia.

02:03.457 --> 02:10.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Unless Mexico is
going to treat
the United States fairly, with
respect, such

02:10.497 --> 02:16.370 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a meeting would be fruitless,
and I want to
go a different route.

02:16.403 --> 02:18.238 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We have no choice.

02:18.271 --> 02:22.876 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: He also
repeated calls to
bolster deportation forces and
eliminate refuges

02:22.909 --> 02:24.711 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for the undocumented.

02:24.745 --> 02:29.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: From day one, I
have said it,
and I mean the immediate removal
of criminal

02:29.950 --> 02:30.917 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
aliens.

02:30.951 --> 02:33.520 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're going to be gone fast.

02:33.553 --> 02:35.088 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

02:35.122 --> 02:42.729 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: And, finally, at
long last cracking
down on sanctuary cities.

02:42.763 --> 02:47.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Outside,
protesters swarmed
the area, opposing the
president's policies

02:48.001 --> 02:50.170 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
on immigration and other issues.

02:50.203 --> 02:54.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Senate Majority Leader Mitch
McConnell
said Congress is prepared to
foot the bill

02:54.875 --> 02:57.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for building the border wall, at
least for
now.

02:57.344 --> 02:58.612 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:58.645 --> 03:00.514 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), Majority
Leader: We
are moving ahead.

03:00.547 --> 03:07.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As the speaker pointed out to
our group yesterday,
with, roughly -- yes roughly $12
billion to

03:07.954 --> 03:08.989 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
$15 billion.

03:09.022 --> 03:13.293 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So we intend to address the wall
issue ourselves.

03:13.326 --> 03:20.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the president can deal with
his relations
with other countries on that
issue and other

03:20.600 --> 03:22.469 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
issues.

03:22.502 --> 03:25.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Later, en route
back to Washington,
White House spokesman Sean
Spicer said the

03:25.672 --> 03:28.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
president wants a 20 percent tax
on all imports
from Mexico.

03:28.975 --> 03:31.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
By doing it that way, we can do
$10 billion

03:31.678 --> 03:34.915 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a year and easily pay for the
wall just through
that mechanism alone.

03:34.948 --> 03:38.885 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But a short
time later, Spicer
said that's just one option.

03:38.919 --> 03:43.857 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At the same time, some
Republicans, like Illinois
Congressman Adam Kinzinger, say
the country

03:43.890 --> 03:46.860 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
still needs a comprehensive
immigration policy.

03:46.893 --> 03:48.728 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:48.762 --> 03:50.897 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM KINZINGER (R), Illinois:
How do we fix
our immigration system so that
in 20, 30 years,

03:50.931 --> 03:52.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
we're not back here again?

03:52.499 --> 03:54.034 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And how do we deal with the
folks that are
here?

03:54.067 --> 03:56.636 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You're not going to round up and
deport 15
million people.

03:56.670 --> 03:58.839 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have to have some kind of a
pathway to
legalization.

03:58.872 --> 04:02.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: There's unease
with some
of President Trump's other
pronouncements

04:02.175 --> 04:03.810 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
as well.

04:03.844 --> 04:07.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
House Speaker Paul Ryan pushed
back today
against Mr. Trump's assertion to
ABC News

04:07.647 --> 04:08.682 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that torture works.

04:08.715 --> 04:10.016 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

04:10.050 --> 04:10.984 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker of the
House: And
torture is illegal.

04:11.017 --> 04:12.385 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And torture is not legal.

04:12.419 --> 04:14.421 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we agree with it not being
legal.

04:14.454 --> 04:19.659 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Mr. Trump did
say he'd defer
his CIA director and incoming
secretary of

04:19.693 --> 04:25.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
defense, both of whom have said
they oppose
a return to water-boarding in
particular.

04:25.098 --> 04:29.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, Mr. Trump returned to
Washington
this afternoon, ending his first
day on Air

04:29.903 --> 04:31.071 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Force One.

04:31.104 --> 04:33.773 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And Lisa joins us
now.

04:33.807 --> 04:39.613 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, Lisa, what are the
Republican members
saying about this White House
talk of an import

04:39.646 --> 04:41.948 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
tax on Mexican goods?

04:41.982 --> 04:45.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: First of all,
they are trying
to get their hands around
exactly what the

04:45.819 --> 04:47.587 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
president is proposing here.

04:47.621 --> 04:51.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We hear from the House speaker's
office that
they believe this is a reference
to the plan

04:51.892 --> 04:56.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
House Republicans laid out last
year called
the Border Adjustability Tax,
and something

04:56.963 --> 04:59.199 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think we're going to talk a
lot about in
the coming months.

04:59.232 --> 05:04.070 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, basically, it is a 20
percent tax not
just on Mexico, but basically on
all imports

05:04.104 --> 05:05.605 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
into this country.

05:05.639 --> 05:09.176 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It would change dramatically how
this country
deals with imports and exports.

05:09.209 --> 05:12.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In affects almost every business
in this country,
a very big deal.

05:12.212 --> 05:18.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Republicans now are trying
to parse out
whether the president is
specifically proposing

05:18.251 --> 05:20.387 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
this, whether it's one idea.

05:20.420 --> 05:23.757 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Exactly what Sean Spicer meant
is still up
in the air at this hour.

05:23.790 --> 05:27.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But House Republicans are hoping
that the
president is full force behind
this plan.

05:27.427 --> 05:28.562 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
They like it.

05:28.595 --> 05:29.996 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Not everyone does.

05:30.030 --> 05:31.765 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's something that we're going
to have to
pay a lot of attention to.

05:31.798 --> 05:33.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: That is for sure.

05:33.733 --> 05:38.972 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, Lisa, as you look back on
the two days
of this conference, what was
actually accomplished?

05:39.005 --> 05:44.377 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Overall, Judy,
the bottom
line here is a timeline.

05:44.411 --> 05:48.882 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The House Republicans have laid
out, specifically
the House, a 200-day agenda.

05:48.915 --> 05:51.017 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
