05:51.051 --> 05:55.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That really means that, by
August, they want
to have in their hands concrete
proposals

05:55.755 --> 06:00.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for how they will replace
Obamacare and how
they will repeal the tax code.

06:00.093 --> 06:01.194 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Now, what does that mean?

06:01.228 --> 06:03.897 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Does that mean they will pass
something by
then?

06:03.930 --> 06:05.765 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
No one's exactly clear.

06:05.799 --> 06:09.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they want to have those
proposals in hand
by August, and Speaker Ryan
today said they

06:09.069 --> 06:11.638 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
want everything passed by the
end of the year.

06:11.671 --> 06:12.739 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Those are ambitious goals.

06:12.772 --> 06:14.241 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The timeline is what we have.

06:14.274 --> 06:16.176 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We don't have the details of the
plans.

06:16.209 --> 06:18.111 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's what they will be doing
for the next
coming months.

06:18.144 --> 06:22.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And so, Lisa,
what are members,
one by one, what are they
telling you in terms

06:22.515 --> 06:24.751 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of whether they think that can
happen?

06:24.784 --> 06:31.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: There are some
nervous members,
because, in addition to these
very large plans,

06:31.091 --> 06:35.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Obamacare and tax reform, they
also have some
things that have tripped up
Republicans in

06:35.128 --> 06:40.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the past, like the debt ceiling,
which will
come due shortly, and also
another government

06:40.233 --> 06:42.068 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
spending bill.

06:42.102 --> 06:44.638 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Those are things that
Republicans have had
trouble with in their own
conference and they

06:44.671 --> 06:46.439 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
take a lot of time.

06:46.473 --> 06:49.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In addition, Judy, they do not
have 60 votes
in the Senate, and I have spoken
to several

06:49.809 --> 06:53.079 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Republicans today who say, we
need to be realistic
about that.

06:53.113 --> 06:57.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We can't push for everything we
want and expect
it, because we know that Senate
Democrats

06:57.484 --> 06:58.918 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
are going to oppose us.

06:58.952 --> 07:03.790 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have to be sober, in the
words of one Republican
I talked to today.

07:03.823 --> 07:07.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa Desjardins,
reporting
from the Republican
congressional retreat

07:07.894 --> 07:10.130 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there in Philadelphia, thank
you.

07:10.163 --> 07:14.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will hear from a senior White
House adviser
right after the news summary.

07:14.601 --> 07:18.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANTONIO MORA: In the day's other
news: Russia
warned President Trump to think
twice about

07:18.838 --> 07:22.442 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
